sentence: Figure 1 details the study selection process.
In Fig. 2, the regional setting of each intervention is shown over a map of HIV rates across states.
Finally, 20 separate interventions met the complete inclusion criteria (see Fig. 1).
Note this adds up to 21 sites; Project Sepa was conducted in Chicago and Florida (See Table 2; Fig. 1).
Figure 2 shows the states HIV incidence rate for Latinas across US, as well as the number of interventions described in this review by state in which they were implemented.

Although rates from areas like Iowa and Minnesota which are New Destination areas along with North and South Carolina, should be interpreted with caution due to low number of cases, Fig. 2 does demonstrate an overall bias in the literature of HIV interventions in traditional Latino settlement and urban areas.
However, none of the interventions reviewed were conducted in the rural areas of the United States, as shown in Fig. 2.

The authors would also like to thank Cindy Miller for her contribution in drafting Fig. 1.References
